-- Australia's Lend Lease sells Bluewater mall, sees earnings boost
-- By Lincoln Feast
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 07:24PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, June 25 (Reuters) - Australian property company Lend Lease Corp <LLC.AX> said on Wednesday it had sold its interest in Bluewater Shopping Centre to Land Securities Group PLC <LAND.L> for 696 million pounds ($1.2 billion), boosting its 2014 earnings by more than 45 percent.

Lend Lease said it now expected a net profit of A$810 million to A$830 million ($761 million to $780 million) for the year and anticipated paying out 50 percent of net profits in unfranked dividends.